The Afrikayam Farm in Strand in the Western Cape is today hosting a special meal for Father’s Day. The all-youth owned restaurant will serve traditional African food especially in honour of Dads. eNCA's Nobesuthu Hejana is covering this story. #dstv403 STRAND - Father’s also want to be shown love and be appreciated: those were sentiments shared at the special Father’s day event hosted by a youth-owned farm restaurant in Strand in the western cape. WATCH: Panel discussion | The essence of fatherhood Special treats like traditional food and music entertainment were on the menu to commemorate the day. It’s a special day to celebrate and remind men of their important role in society. Mentorship and being positive role models are some of the values that young fathers want all men to practice. This also with love and support from society at large. Bulelani Ndabeni said, "the most important thing about celebrating Father’s Days, it's to encourage young father in my generation. It strengthens us especially when you’re recognised in your community and that also motivates one to only want to do good by the people. ” While the special treat on the menu was traditional food. Normal meals were served at half price and all Ingredients are freshly picked from the garden. Afrikayam Farm restaurant owner Mawande Sigwinta said, "the importance of father in the society is important in grooming the boy child to understand that masculinity is not a way to go about things in addressing issues, either with females or any gender. Fathers are very important and they should be celebrated and be reminded that they are part of the society. ”